model

Class Arithmetic

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.Arithmetic
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Clause, PCExpression

    public class Arithmetic
extends Object
implements Clause
    This class represents arithmetic expressions. It is a binary operator. It extends Clause.

    Arithmetic expressions are only comparisons between numbers. Their operands must be bound before evaluation.

    Author:
    Alexandre Camus

        public ArithmeticSolutionNode getSolver(RuleSet rules,
                               SubstitutionSet parentSolution,
                               AbstractSolutionNode parentNode)
        Creates a solver which is a node in the tree proof. This is the version for the arithmetic expression.
